1
00:00:41,439 --> 00:00:42,159
Baby.

2
00:00:42,439 --> 00:00:44,079
I'll come pick you up tonight.

3
00:00:46,159 --> 00:00:46,960
Be good.

4
00:00:47,799 --> 00:00:48,479
Bye-bye.

5
00:00:48,479 --> 00:00:48,840
Bye.

6
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:49,679
See you tonight.

7
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:00,240
Bye-bye.

8
00:01:01,960 --> 00:01:02,520
Ying Tang.

9
00:01:03,240 --> 00:01:04,040
Ying Tang.

10
00:01:04,239 --> 00:01:05,040
Ying Tang.

11
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:09,239
Xiaochuan.

12
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:10,840
What are you doing here?

13
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:12,319
You...

14
00:01:12,799 --> 00:01:13,959
Didn't I tell you...

15
00:01:13,959 --> 00:01:16,280
...not to come to school looking for me if it's not important?

16
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:18,439
Didn't you say you have exams coming up soon?

17
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:19,920
I just wanted to come see you.

18
00:01:19,920 --> 00:01:21,879
Look, I brought you some Triangular rice cakes.

19
00:01:23,239 --> 00:01:24,040
I don't want them.

20
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:26,719
Who wants to eat cheap stuff like this?

21
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:28,120
I told you already.

22
00:01:28,120 --> 00:01:29,519
I'm going to go to college.

23
00:01:29,799 --> 00:01:31,239
You didn't even finish middle school.

24
00:01:31,599 --> 00:01:32,680
It's impossible between us.

25
00:01:33,439 --> 00:01:34,079
Ying Tang.

26
00:01:34,519 --> 00:01:35,959
I know I'm not good enough for you.

27
00:01:36,079 --> 00:01:38,040
But I'll definitely work hard to make more money.

28
00:01:38,159 --> 00:01:39,400
To give you a good life.

29
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:40,879
Anyway, after I graduate from college...

30
00:01:40,879 --> 00:01:42,319
...I'm definitely staying in the city.

31
00:01:42,959 --> 00:01:44,519
If you can buy an apartment in the city...

32
00:01:44,879 --> 00:01:46,040
...I'll think about it.

33
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:48,959
You should go back.

34
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:50,239
I have to go back to class.

35
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:14,039
You cleaned this place up pretty nicely.

36
00:02:14,479 --> 00:02:15,479
No big deal.

37
00:02:19,639 --> 00:02:20,520
Sister Yingrong.

38
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:21,960
From now on...

39
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:22,719
...I'm going to work with you...

40
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:24,080
...here in the vinegar workshop.

41
00:02:25,639 --> 00:02:27,280
I don't have money to pay you.

42
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:27,960
No need.

43
00:02:28,319 --> 00:02:28,879
Paying off debt.

44
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:30,759
But right now, I don't even know...

45
00:02:30,759 --> 00:02:32,039
...if I can make this work.

46
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:33,840
Aren't you afraid of losing out by following me?

47
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:36,479
I think you're someone who gets things done.

48
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:38,159
I have to pay you back anyway.

49
00:02:38,599 --> 00:02:39,280
Besides...

50
00:02:40,639 --> 00:02:41,759
...I accept you as my boss.

51
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:46,280
You right now...

52
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:48,039
...look a bit like you did when we were kids.

53
00:02:54,479 --> 00:02:56,199
I think if you want to expand your vinegar workshop...

54
00:02:57,159 --> 00:02:58,280
...you might be short-handed.

55
00:02:59,039 --> 00:03:00,360
Why don't you ask my brothers?

56
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:01,879
We can work together.

57
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,080
Having labor is great, of course.

58
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:05,560
But...

59
00:03:06,159 --> 00:03:08,039
...I don't just take anyone.

60
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,199
Let me think about it.

61
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:15,680
I forgot to tell your brother...

62
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:17,240
...someone is looking for him to repair a machine.

63
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:20,240
Darn it, darn it, darn it.

64
00:03:25,439 --> 00:03:26,759
Way to go, Zheng Minjiang.

65
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,800
What are you talking about out of the blue?

66
00:03:30,759 --> 00:03:31,919
I heard from Boss Wang...

67
00:03:31,919 --> 00:03:34,080
...that a Boss Tang is looking for you to fix a machine.

68
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:35,400
Asking about you everywhere.

69
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:38,120
Tang?

70
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:41,800
I see.

71
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:44,919
I heard that Boss Tang runs a factory.

72
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:47,599
If you fix it, you could make a lot of money.

73
00:03:47,599 --> 00:03:48,400
I'm not going.

74
00:03:48,639 --> 00:03:49,680
Whoever wants to go can go.

75
00:03:53,159 --> 00:03:54,280
Are you stupid?

76
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:57,280
Fixing machines not only proves your technical skills...

77
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:58,360
...but also earns money to pay off debts.

78
00:03:58,360 --> 00:03:59,560
Why won't you go?

79
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,960
Are you afraid you can't fix it?

80
00:04:05,319 --> 00:04:06,280
And don't dare to go?

81
00:04:08,719 --> 00:04:09,840
Can't I just not want to go?

82
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:21,879
Here.

83
00:04:26,519 --> 00:04:27,600
Are you crazy?

84
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:30,240
Why give me attitude for no reason?

85
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:40,800
What took you so long?

86
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:42,079
Come over here and eat.

87
00:04:42,519 --> 00:04:43,120
Mom.

88
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,160
I'm not in the mood to eat today.

89
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:45,120
Just leave me alone.

90
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,199
What kind of talk is that?

91
00:04:47,399 --> 00:04:49,160
It's your birthday today.

92
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:51,560
You can't let your mom's kindness go to waste.

93
00:04:52,199 --> 00:04:52,839
Mom.

94
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:55,319
You know it's my birthday?

95
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:01,120
And there's my favorite...

96
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:02,920
...stewed meat and mung bean cakes.

97
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,279
What kind of mother...

98
00:05:05,279 --> 00:05:07,120
...wouldn't know her own child's birthday?

99
00:05:08,079 --> 00:05:08,480
Here.

100
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,279
Your favorite braised pork.

101
00:05:10,279 --> 00:05:10,680
Look.

102
00:05:10,759 --> 00:05:11,160
Here.

103
00:05:11,279 --> 00:05:12,040
Let Mom serve you.

104
00:05:12,439 --> 00:05:12,680
Here.

105
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:14,279
Eat up.

106
00:05:16,639 --> 00:05:17,680
And the mung bean cakes.

107
00:05:19,839 --> 00:05:20,800
Take your time.

108
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:25,399
Mom.

109
00:05:25,839 --> 00:05:28,240
So you do have me in your heart.

110
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:30,279
Thank you.

111
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:31,439
For what?

112
00:05:32,199 --> 00:05:33,279
Mom treats you well...

113
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:34,920
...so you need to treat Little Sister well.

114
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,959
That's the only way our family will flourish...

115
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:39,600
...and get rich.

116
00:05:41,319 --> 00:05:42,160
Sanmei?

117
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,360
What's wrong with her now?

118
00:05:46,079 --> 00:05:47,639
Nothing's really wrong.

119
00:05:47,839 --> 00:05:49,800
It's just that the clothes your little sister wears...

120
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,439
...she's been wearing them for so long.

121
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,240
You should bring some money home...

122
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:56,079
...to buy her a few new outfits.

123
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:58,439
It would also make our family look good.

124
00:06:00,839 --> 00:06:02,480
So you celebrating my birthday...

125
00:06:03,439 --> 00:06:04,720
...was just to get money out of me.

126
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:11,199
I knew it.

127
00:06:11,839 --> 00:06:12,680
After all these years...

128
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:14,079
...you've never celebrated my birthday.

129
00:06:14,199 --> 00:06:15,319
Why suddenly this year?

130
00:06:18,839 --> 00:06:20,240
Turns out it's still for Little Sister.

131
00:06:24,399 --> 00:06:25,439
You gave birth to Little Sister...

132
00:06:25,439 --> 00:06:27,079
...but didn't you give birth to me too?

133
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:28,759
Do you care about me only because...

134
00:06:28,759 --> 00:06:30,279
...I'm a tool for making money?

135
00:06:32,759 --> 00:06:33,959
Watch your mouth.

136
00:06:34,079 --> 00:06:35,360
I am your mother.

137
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:37,800
Why won't you listen to a word I say?

138
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,000
Drinking alone?

139
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:09,000
Give me a bottle too.

140
00:07:09,639 --> 00:07:10,879
Why should I give you any?

141
00:07:18,399 --> 00:07:19,480
Today, I was the one...

142
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:21,920
...who lost my temper and snapped at you.

143
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:24,360
I'm sorry.

144
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:27,279
Don't be mad anymore.

145
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:30,480
Master Zheng is so capable...

146
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:31,839
...yet he's apologizing to me.

147
00:07:58,839 --> 00:07:59,800
Zheng Minjiang

148
00:08:00,839 --> 00:08:02,360
Actually, you don't need to be afraid.

149
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:07,160
Why are you suddenly comforting me?

150
00:08:09,279 --> 00:08:11,519
You know, even though you're not that great,

151
00:08:12,199 --> 00:08:12,800
but...

152
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:16,480
there's definitely no doubt about your ability.

153
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:18,319
You have to have confidence in yourself.

154
00:08:20,959 --> 00:08:21,879
I am afraid.

155
00:08:22,519 --> 00:08:23,920
You think I really don't dare to go?

156
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:26,199
It's because over there, there's someone

157
00:08:26,199 --> 00:08:27,279
I don't want to see.

158
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,160
Okay, okay, okay.

159
00:08:29,519 --> 00:08:30,399
Let's just say that's the reason.

160
00:08:31,199 --> 00:08:32,960
So, are you going to let that person you don't want to see

161
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,279
hold back your future?

162
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:41,879
There's nothing wrong with admitting you're scared.

163
00:08:42,879 --> 00:08:43,679
Let me tell you,

164
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:45,159
before...

165
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:47,639
only before...

166
00:08:48,559 --> 00:08:51,320
I had a tiny little bit of...

167
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:52,120
admiration for you.

168
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:54,879
Just a tiny smidge.

169
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:57,639
Back then,

170
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:59,840
I thought you were good at studying,

171
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:01,240
and after joining the factory,

172
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:02,879
your skills were good too.

173
00:09:03,039 --> 00:09:03,879
It's just that...

174
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:06,039
you have a sharp tongue,

175
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,000
you're getting old,

176
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,039
and your eloquence isn't getting any better.

177
00:09:10,639 --> 00:09:11,360
Stop right there.

178
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,759
Are you praising me or scolding me?

179
00:09:15,759 --> 00:09:17,519
Anyway, what I mean is,

180
00:09:17,879 --> 00:09:19,279
you don't need to worry.

181
00:09:19,799 --> 00:09:21,720
If I had those skills of yours,

182
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:22,879
I'd have a hundred ways

183
00:09:22,879 --> 00:09:24,559
to make a fortune.

184
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:27,279
So, what about later?

185
00:09:28,399 --> 00:09:29,279
What do you plan to do?

186
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:30,399
Keep raising pigs?

187
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:32,000
I want to make money.

188
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:34,000
I want to make a lot of money.

189
00:09:35,039 --> 00:09:36,320
Money-grubber.

190
00:09:36,639 --> 00:09:38,000
What kind of girl

191
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:39,720
thinks about making money every day?

192
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:41,639
I, Wang Yingrong, am not someone

193
00:09:41,639 --> 00:09:43,039
who lives a quiet life.

194
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:45,240
I want to live a bold and adventurous life.

195
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:46,879
I want to make big money,

196
00:09:46,879 --> 00:09:48,879
so everyone looks up to me.

197
00:09:54,799 --> 00:09:56,759
This letter... I think...

198
00:09:57,759 --> 00:09:58,879
I know.

199
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,440
You like my sister.

200
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:01,799
I'll go back and tell her right now.

201
00:10:02,879 --> 00:10:03,360
Yingrong!

202
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:04,960
Don't worry.

203
00:10:05,039 --> 00:10:06,360
My sister talks about you all the time.

204
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:07,840
You two will definitely work out.

205
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:08,799
I...

206
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:14,480
Who said I like your sister?

207
00:10:16,399 --> 00:10:18,000
It's obviously you that I like.

208
00:10:28,679 --> 00:10:29,639
What's wrong with you?

209
00:10:29,799 --> 00:10:30,840
Did you drink too much?

210
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:34,480
This wine isn't bad.

211
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:37,240
Of course, I picked it myself.

212
00:10:39,279 --> 00:10:41,080
Since it's the wine you picked yourself,

213
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:42,440
might as well drink it.

214
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:43,559
I'll drink first.

215
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:45,159
I'll drink first.

216
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:06,039
Good wine.

217
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:11,000
Good wine.

218
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:16,120
Can't stop drinking good wine.

219
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:18,600
Let's go.

220
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:20,039
Let's go drink at your place.

221
00:11:20,679 --> 00:11:21,919
Drink at my place?

222
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:23,759
Sure.

223
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:24,919
You wait.

224
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,840
I'll go back and open the door for you.

225
00:11:29,679 --> 00:11:30,679
I'm going home.

226
00:11:31,039 --> 00:11:31,559
Going home.

227
00:11:34,679 --> 00:11:35,480
Home, home.

228
00:11:36,679 --> 00:11:37,840
That way.

229
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:38,480
Right.

230
00:11:42,559 --> 00:11:43,480
Wait.

231
00:12:03,879 --> 00:12:04,360
Get up

232
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:07,720
Good wine is like life

233
00:12:08,039 --> 00:12:10,080
Getting rich starts today

234
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:11,000
Get up

235
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:13,600
Right

236
00:12:13,879 --> 00:12:14,360
No

237
00:12:14,519 --> 00:12:15,879
What are you doing this late at night?

238
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:17,600
Get up

239
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:20,440
Ying... Sister Yingrong

240
00:12:20,639 --> 00:12:22,200
Why are you in my room? Aren't you afraid of my mom?

241
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,039
Shut up

242
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:24,799
If you want to make money

243
00:12:24,799 --> 00:12:25,399
Come with me

244
00:12:25,519 --> 00:12:26,399
Let's go. Get up

245
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:28,960
Hurry up

246
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:29,919
Wait a second

247
00:12:29,919 --> 00:12:31,039
Let me put on some pants

248
00:12:33,759 --> 00:12:34,440
Put them on

249
00:12:34,879 --> 00:12:35,559
Go ahead

250
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:37,600
Put them on

251
00:12:45,039 --> 00:12:46,600
Who's gonna come?

252
00:12:55,559 --> 00:12:56,360
Go, go, go

253
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:57,080
Let's go

254
00:12:57,440 --> 00:12:58,480
Go, go, let's go!

255
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:10,120
This is where we get rich

256
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:15,799
This is the money from selling my motorcycle

257
00:13:15,799 --> 00:13:18,559
And all my savings are here too

258
00:13:18,799 --> 00:13:20,159
I'm asking you

259
00:13:20,159 --> 00:13:21,879
Zheng Haiyang and Zheng Xiaochuan

260
00:13:22,799 --> 00:13:23,600
You two

261
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:25,600
Are you making vinegar with me or not?

262
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:26,480
Making vinegar?

263
00:13:27,039 --> 00:13:28,240
You want to run a vinegar workshop?

264
00:13:30,039 --> 00:13:31,000
Can't I?

265
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:33,399
Are you okay?

266
00:13:34,639 --> 00:13:36,480
You went from fishing to raising pigs before

267
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:37,759
And nothing came of it

268
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:38,960
The way I see it

269
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,120
You're just not cut out for business

270
00:13:42,559 --> 00:13:43,120
Sister

271
00:13:43,399 --> 00:13:44,159
How about

272
00:13:45,519 --> 00:13:46,960
I take you to the hospital for a checkup?

273
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:50,080
You're the one who's sick

274
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:54,879
I've never been more clear-headed in my life

275
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:56,240
Sister Yingrong

276
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:58,240
Have you forgotten how Second Aunt went crazy?

277
00:13:58,679 --> 00:13:59,720
You know, right?

278
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:01,679
Wasn't it because of this private vinegar workshop?

279
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:03,279
And profiteering?

280
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:09,000
Listen. Stop sleeping

281
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,320
Let me tell you

282
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:16,879
The policies have changed now

283
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:20,519
I've been going to Uncle Fang's shop a lot lately

284
00:14:21,279 --> 00:14:22,519
Guess what?

285
00:14:22,879 --> 00:14:24,080
What?

286
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:26,159
Business is extremely good

287
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:29,000
